[[=]]
+ [[size 250%]]CALIBOLD[[/size]]
[[/=]]

For every person who says that Calibold is a criminally underrated author, there's another who believes that he is nothing more than an embarrassment to the SCP community. Of course, both of these very real people are correct. I've been writing for SCP since 2019, and have made several contributions, such as...

* creating the [[[Decom. Dept. Hub|Decommissioning Department]]].
* winning second place in the [[[Exquisite Corpse Contest]]] with Yossipossi --carrying-- coauthoring our entry, [[[SCP-5545|SCP-5545 — 𝙰 𝙱 𝙽 𝙾 𝚁 𝙼 𝙰 𝙻 𝙸 𝚃 𝚈]]].
* contributing to the unofficial [http://scp-un.wikidot.com/translation-hub#toc18 Latin branch] of the SCP wiki.
* winning the SCP-7000 Contest's "Most Disliked By People With Good Taste" award with Sherf for our entry [[[SCP-7400|SCP-7400 — Your Honor, League of Legends]]].
* writing the highest rated [[[SCP Anthology Hub|SCP Anthology 2022]]] article with [[[SCP-7179|SCP-7179 — E is for Eternity]]].
* winning second place in the [[[PDContest2025|Public Domain Contest]]] with HarryBlank and Nico.

But of course, I do more than just write for this site. I've coauthored a non-SCP book which should be releasing around mid-2025. Outside of my actual job, I regularly play D&D, and I occasionally do some silly CSS and graphic design stuff. You can also catch me on the Pokémon Showdown ladder, either in OU if I'm feeling brave, or Random Battles if I'm not.

