"Loved every minute. Your writing is so consistently clean, clear and polished that it's never anything but a joy to read, and this never feels even half its length. It's a very fun romp with a strong emotional core, and the two halves of the story keep pace with each other in a way that's really difficult to balance. The sheer absurdity of the SPC, the infernal sleaziness of Undervegas, and whatever that last location was all work together to emphasize what a bizarre new world Robinson has walked into, and he keeps on walking because despite all the craziness this is at its core a story about a man who wants to help his grandmother. That's beautiful as a concept, and the execution intensifies the beauty. You did a fantastic job, Cal, and it's great to see you writing again."

//-- HarryBlank, on SCP-8228//

